searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative","doc":"Native Elixir provider for ExWaha вҖ” no WAHA Docker container required.\n\nTalks the WhatsApp Multi-Device protocol via [`whatsmeow`](https://github.com/tulir/whatsmeow),\na Go library, running as a single supervised sidecar process per BEAM node.\nCommunication happens over stdio with length-prefixed JSON frames.","ref":"ExWahaNative.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Status - ExWahaNative","doc":"v0.1.0 ships the architecture: supervision tree, wire protocol, Bridge\nGenServer, per-session GenServer, mix task to build the Go binary, and a\nGo skeleton that compiles. The actual whatsmeow integration on the Go side\nis a TODO вҖ” see `README.md` for the development plan.","ref":"ExWahaNative.html#module-status"},{"type":"module","title":"Why this exists - ExWahaNative","doc":"`:ex_waha` (the wrapper) requires running a separate WAHA Docker container.\nThat works but adds operational overhead. `:ex_waha_native` runs everything\ninside your BEAM release: one Go binary in `priv/`, no extra containers,\nno HTTP between you and WhatsApp.","ref":"ExWahaNative.html#module-why-this-exists"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - ExWahaNative","doc":"account = ExWahaNative.Account.new(session: \"profile_42\")\n    {:ok, _pid} = ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.ensure_started(account)\n\n    # Same facade as the WAHA / Meta providers\n    ExWaha.send_text(account, \"+201001234567\", \"Hello!\")","ref":"ExWahaNative.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative.Account","doc":"An account on the native (whatsmeow) provider.\n\nUnlike `ExWaha.Providers.Waha.Account` there is no remote server URL;\nthe Go binary runs locally inside the BEAM node. Sessions are identified\nby their `session_name`.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Account.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWahaNative.Account.t/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Account.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Account.new/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Account.html#new/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative.Bridge","doc":"GenServer that owns the Go bridge `Port` and routes traffic between\nElixir callers and the whatsmeow process.\n\n  * Outbound: serializes `%{op, args}` requests to length-prefixed JSON,\n    stores `ref -> from` for the reply.\n  * Inbound: stream-decodes frames; routes `response` to the awaiting\n    caller, dispatches `event` to the session GenServer.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Crash semantics - ExWahaNative.Bridge","doc":"If the Port closes (Go process died), this GenServer exits. Its supervisor\nrestarts it, which re-spawns the Go binary. whatsmeow re-connects every\nsession from sqlstore. In-flight requests get `{:error, :bridge_restart}`.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.html#module-crash-semantics"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.call/5","doc":"Synchronously send a request to the Go bridge and await its response.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.html#call/5"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.cast/4","doc":"Fire-and-forget op.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.html#cast/4"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Bridge.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative.Provider","doc":"`ExWaha.Provider` implementation that routes through the Go bridge.\n\nRegistered with `ExWaha.Provider.register/2` at application start so that\n`ExWaha.send_text(native_account, ...)` dispatches here transparently.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Provider.html"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative.Session","doc":"Per-WhatsApp-account state machine.\n\nHolds the account, current status, and a set of subscribers (LiveViews,\nPubSub bridges, custom handlers) that get `{:ex_waha_native, kind, payload}`\nmessages on every event from the Go bridge for this session.\n\nOutbound calls are routed through `ExWahaNative.Bridge`; this GenServer\ndoesn't serialize them вҖ” the Bridge does.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.status/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.logout/1","doc":"Log the device out at the protocol level вҖ” wipes the paired session on\nthe WhatsApp servers and clears local state. After this the next `start`\ntriggers a fresh QR/pairing flow.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#logout/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.qr/1","doc":"Returns the most recent QR code seen for the session, or `nil` if none.\n\nWhen the account is unpaired, the bridge emits successive `qr` events as\nthe underlying WhatsApp QR rotates every ~20s. This helper exposes the\nlatest one so a controller/LiveView can render it without subscribing.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#qr/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.request_pairing_code/2","doc":"Request a phone-pairing code instead of QR.\n\nWhatsApp 2.24+ supports linking a device via a numeric pairing code shown\non the phone. Returns `{:ok, code}` (formatted as e.g. `\"ABCD-EFGH\"`) or\nan `{:error, reason}` if the session is not in a state to pair.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#request_pairing_code/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.status/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#status/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.stop/1","doc":"Stop the session GenServer (closes the device locally but does not\ninvalidate the WhatsApp pairing вҖ” `start` will reconnect).","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#stop/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.subscribe/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.html#subscribe/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Registry","doc":"Process registry for `ExWahaNative.Session` instances, keyed by session name.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Registry.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Registry.lookup/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Registry.html#lookup/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Registry.via/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Registry.html#via/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor","doc":"DynamicSupervisor for per-account `ExWahaNative.Session` processes.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.ensure_started/2","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.html#ensure_started/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.stop/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.html#stop/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExWahaNative.Wire","doc":"Length-prefixed JSON framing for the Bridge вҶ” Go process protocol.\n\nFrame format on the wire:\n\n    < >\n\nPayloads are JSON. Three message kinds:","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Request (Elixir вҶ’ Go) - ExWahaNative.Wire","doc":"%{\n      \"type\" => \"request\",\n      \"ref\"  => \" \",\n      \"session\" => \"profile_42\",\n      \"op\"   => \"send_text\",\n      \"args\" => %{...}\n    }","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#module-request-elixir-go"},{"type":"module","title":"Response (Go вҶ’ Elixir, correlated by ref) - ExWahaNative.Wire","doc":"%{\n      \"type\" => \"response\",\n      \"ref\"  => \" \",\n      \"ok\"   => true,\n      \"result\" => %{...}\n    }\n\n    %{\n      \"type\" => \"response\",\n      \"ref\"  => \" \",\n      \"ok\"   => false,\n      \"error\" => \"...\",\n      \"code\"  => \"...\"\n    }","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#module-response-go-elixir-correlated-by-ref"},{"type":"module","title":"Event (Go вҶ’ Elixir, no ref, server-initiated) - ExWahaNative.Wire","doc":"%{\n      \"type\" => \"event\",\n      \"session\" => \"profile_42\",\n      \"kind\"    => \"message\" | \"qr\" | \"paired\" | \"disconnected\" | ...,\n      \"payload\" => %{...}\n    }","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#module-event-go-elixir-no-ref-server-initiated"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWahaNative.Wire.frame/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#t:frame/0"},{"type":"type","title":"ExWahaNative.Wire.message/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#t:message/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Wire.decode_stream/2","doc":"Stream-decode bytes from the Port.\n\nReturns `{messages, leftover}` вҖ” call again with the leftover prepended to\nthe next chunk.","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#decode_stream/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Wire.encode!/1","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#encode!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExWahaNative.Wire.new_ref/0","doc":"","ref":"ExWahaNative.Wire.html#new_ref/0"},{"type":"task","title":"mix ex_waha_native.build_native","doc":"Build the Go bridge binary.\n\nCompiles `native/bridge` into `priv/native/whatsmeow_bridge`. Requires the\nGo toolchain (`go` вүҘ 1.21) on PATH.\n\n    mix ex_waha_native.build_native","ref":"Mix.Tasks.ExWahaNative.BuildNative.html"},{"type":"task","title":"Options - mix ex_waha_native.build_native","doc":"* `--target TRIPLE` вҖ” cross-compile (e.g. `linux/amd64`, `darwin/arm64`).\n    Defaults to the host platform.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.ExWahaNative.BuildNative.html#module-options"},{"type":"task","title":"Output - mix ex_waha_native.build_native","doc":"The compiled binary is placed at `priv/native/whatsmeow_bridge`. This path\nis what `ExWahaNative.Bridge` looks up at runtime via\n`Application.app_dir/2`.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.ExWahaNative.BuildNative.html#module-output"},{"type":"extras","title":"ExWahaNative","doc":"# ExWahaNative\n\n[![Hex.pm](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/ex_waha_native.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_waha_native)\n[![Documentation](https://img.shields.io/badge/hex-docs-lightgreen.svg)](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_waha_native)\n\nNative [`ex_waha`](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_waha) provider that talks the\nWhatsApp Multi-Device protocol directly via [`whatsmeow`](https://github.com/tulir/whatsmeow)\n(Go), running as a single supervised sidecar process inside your BEAM node.\n**No WAHA Docker container required.**\n\n> **Status: 0.2.0 wires whatsmeow into the Go side.** The bridge now opens\n> real WhatsApp sessions through `go.mau.fi/whatsmeow`, supports QR pairing\n> and phone pairing codes, sends text, emits `qr` / `paired` / `connected`\n> / `message` / `message_ack` events, and persists devices in SQLite. See\n> the [Roadmap](#roadmap) for what's next.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Why this exists - ExWahaNative","doc":"`:ex_waha` (the wrapper) requires running the WAHA Docker container as a\nsidecar. That works but means an extra service to deploy, monitor, and\nrestart. `:ex_waha_native` replaces WAHA with a Go binary in your release's\n`priv/` directory:\n\n```\nyour_app release\nв””в”Җв”Җ priv/\n    в””в”Җв”Җ ex_waha_native/\n        в””в”Җв”Җ native/\n            в””в”Җв”Җ whatsmeow_bridge          # statically-linked Go binary\n                                           # one process per BEAM node\n```\n\nOne binary, no HTTP, no Docker. Sessions live in SQLite (per session) or\nPostgres (shared) via whatsmeow's sqlstore.","ref":"readme.html#why-this-exists"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - ExWahaNative","doc":"```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:ex_waha, \"~> 0.1.0\"},\n    {:ex_waha_native, \"~> 0.1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nYou also need the **Go toolchain** (вүҘ 1.21) on the build machine. After\n`mix deps.get`:\n\n```bash\nmix ex_waha_native.build_native\n```\n\nThis compiles `native/bridge/*.go` to `priv/native/whatsmeow_bridge`.\nCross-compile for your deploy target with `--target linux/amd64`.","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Usage - ExWahaNative","doc":"```elixir\n# Tell the application to start the bridge GenServer\nconfig :ex_waha_native, start_bridge: true\n\n# Build an account\naccount = %ExWahaNative.Account{\n  session: \"profile_42\",\n  store: {:sqlite, \"priv/sessions/profile_42.db\"},\n  bridge: ExWahaNative.Bridge\n}\n\n# Bring under supervision (spawns the whatsmeow client, emits QR via event)\n{:ok, _pid} = ExWahaNative.Session.Supervisor.ensure_started(account)\n\n# Subscribe to events for this session\nExWahaNative.Session.subscribe(account)\n\n# First time: render the QR. Subsequent runs reconnect from sqlstore.\nreceive do\n  {:ex_waha_native, :qr, %{\"code\" => code}} -> render_qr(code)\nend\n\nreceive do\n  {:ex_waha_native, :paired, %{\"phone\" => phone}} -> IO.puts(\"paired as #{phone}\")\nend\n\n# Same facade as the WAHA / Meta providers\nExWaha.send_text(account, \"+201001234567\", \"Hello!\")\n```","ref":"readme.html#usage"},{"type":"extras","title":"Phone pairing code (no QR scanner) - ExWahaNative","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, \"ABCD-EFGH\"} =\n  ExWahaNative.Session.request_pairing_code(account, \"+201001234567\")\n# Enter the code on the WhatsApp app: Linked Devices -> Link with phone number.\n```","ref":"readme.html#phone-pairing-code-no-qr-scanner"},{"type":"extras","title":"Polling status / latest QR - ExWahaNative","doc":"```elixir\n:scan_qr = ExWahaNative.Session.status(account)\n\"2@...\" = ExWahaNative.Session.qr(account)\n```","ref":"readme.html#polling-status-latest-qr"},{"type":"extras","title":"Logging out / stopping - ExWahaNative","doc":"```elixir\n:ok = ExWahaNative.Session.logout(account)   # invalidates the WhatsApp pairing\n:ok = ExWahaNative.Session.stop(account)     # local-only close, can resume\n```","ref":"readme.html#logging-out-stopping"},{"type":"extras","title":"Architecture - ExWahaNative","doc":"```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ  Elixir host application                             в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  ExWaha.send_text(native_account, ...)               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в”Ӯ                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в–ј                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  ExWaha.Provider dispatch (registry, runtime)        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в”Ӯ                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в–ј                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  ExWahaNative.Provider                               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в”Ӯ                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в–ј                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  ExWahaNative.SessionSupervisor                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”ң Session profile_42 (GenServer)                    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”ң Session profile_43                                в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”” ...                                               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в”Ӯ                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ           в–ј                                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  ExWahaNative.Bridge (Port GenServer)                в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   length-prefixed JSON over stdio                    в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                      в”Ӯ Port (stdin/stdout)\n                      в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ  priv/native/whatsmeow_bridge (Go binary)            в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  - tulir/whatsmeow client per session                в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  - sqlstore (SQLite or Postgres)                     в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  - event loop fans events back to Elixir             в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                      в”Ӯ WhatsApp Multi-Device protocol\n                      в–ј\n                 WhatsApp servers\n```","ref":"readme.html#architecture"},{"type":"extras","title":"Process model - ExWahaNative","doc":"- **One Go process per BEAM node**, multiplexed by `session` field.\n  Memory-efficient; mirrors how `whatsmeow` itself is designed.\n- **One Elixir `Session` GenServer per WhatsApp account.** Owns subscriber\n  list, current status, last QR.\n- **One `Bridge` GenServer.** Owns the `Port`, correlates request/response\n  refs, routes async events to the right `Session`.","ref":"readme.html#process-model"},{"type":"extras","title":"Crash semantics - ExWahaNative","doc":"If the Go process dies:\n1. The Port closes; `Bridge` exits with `{:bridge_exit, status}`.\n2. `ExWahaNative.Supervisor` (one_for_one) restarts `Bridge`.\n3. The Go binary re-spawns and re-loads sessions from sqlstore.\n4. In-flight requests get `{:error, :bridge_exited}`.\n5. `Session` GenServers stay alive вҖ” they re-establish via subsequent\n   calls.\n\nIf a single `Session` crashes, only that session is affected; the Bridge\nand other Sessions continue.","ref":"readme.html#crash-semantics"},{"type":"extras","title":"Wire protocol - ExWahaNative","doc":"Length-prefixed JSON. See `ExWahaNative.Wire` for the canonical reference.\n\n```\n[4-byte big-endian length][UTF-8 JSON body]\n```\n\nThree message kinds:\n\n```json\n// Elixir -> Go\n{\"type\":\"request\", \"ref\":\" \", \"session\":\"profile_42\",\n \"op\":\"send_text\", \"args\":{\"to\":\"201001234567@s.whatsapp.net\", \"text\":\"hi\"}}\n\n// Go -> Elixir, correlated\n{\"type\":\"response\", \"ref\":\" \", \"ok\":true, \"result\":{\"id\":\"3EB0...\"}}\n\n// Go -> Elixir, async\n{\"type\":\"event\", \"session\":\"profile_42\", \"kind\":\"message\",\n \"payload\":{\"from\":\"201001234567@s.whatsapp.net\", \"body\":\"hello\"}}\n```","ref":"readme.html#wire-protocol"},{"type":"extras","title":"Building the Go binary - ExWahaNative","doc":"The `mix ex_waha_native.build_native` task wraps `go build`:\n\n```bash\n# Native build\nmix ex_waha_native.build_native\n\n# Cross-compile for production\nmix ex_waha_native.build_native --target linux/amd64\nmix ex_waha_native.build_native --target darwin/arm64\n```\n\nOutput lands in `priv/native/whatsmeow_bridge`. Add this path to your\nrelease:\n\n```elixir\n# rel/overlays/... or include in :files for the package\n```\n\nPre-built binaries for common targets will ship via GitHub releases once\nthe project is past 0.1.0.","ref":"readme.html#building-the-go-binary"},{"type":"extras","title":"Roadmap - ExWahaNative","doc":"| Version | Scope |\n|---|---|\n| **0.1.0** | Architecture: supervision tree, wire protocol, Elixir Bridge & Session GenServers, mix task, Go skeleton with `ping` op + stub handlers |\n| **0.2.0** (current) | whatsmeow integration in Go: `open_session`, QR + phone-code pairing, `send_text`, `logout`, message + receipt + connection events |\n| **0.3.0** | Media (`send_image`, `send_video`, `send_document`, `send_audio`); presence and typing events |\n| **0.4.0** | Group operations; multi-device sync; history sync |\n| **0.5.0** | Postgres sqlstore for multi-node BEAM clusters; session migration |\n| **0.6.0** | Pre-built binary distribution via GitHub releases (no Go toolchain required for users) |","ref":"readme.html#roadmap"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - ExWahaNative","doc":"MIT for the Elixir code. See the LICENSE file. The Go bridge depends on\n[whatsmeow](https://github.com/tulir/whatsmeow) which is **MPL-2.0** вҖ”\nreview their license before redistributing the compiled binary.","ref":"readme.html#license"},{"type":"extras","title":"Disclaimer - ExWahaNative","doc":"WhatsApp's Terms of Service do not permit unofficial clients. Using\n`whatsmeow` (and therefore this package) on a production WhatsApp account\ncarries real risk of account ban. Read\n[`ex_waha`'s safety guide](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_waha/safety_and_bans.html)\nbefore going to production. For commercial use cases consider Meta's\nofficial Cloud API via `ExWaha.Providers.Meta`.","ref":"readme.html#disclaimer"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changelog","doc":"# Changelog\n\n## [0.2.0] - 2026-04-27","ref":"changelog.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Added - Changelog","doc":"- Real `whatsmeow` integration in the Go bridge: `open_session`, QR\n  pairing flow, phone-pairing-code flow, `send_text`, `logout`,\n  `close_session`.\n- Event mapping from whatsmeow to the bridge protocol вҖ” `qr`, `paired`,\n  `connected`, `disconnected`, `logged_out`, `message`, `message_ack`,\n  `offline_sync_completed`.\n- SQLite session persistence via `modernc.org/sqlite` (pure Go, no CGo).\n  In-memory store available via `:memory` for tests.\n- `ExWahaNative.Session.qr/1` вҖ” read latest QR string from the session.\n- `ExWahaNative.Session.request_pairing_code/2` вҖ” link without QR.\n- `ExWahaNative.Session.logout/1` вҖ” invalidate the WhatsApp pairing.\n- `ExWahaNative.Session.stop/1` вҖ” close the local session without logging\n  out.\n- `examples/03_send_via_native.exs` вҖ” end-to-end pair + send walkthrough.","ref":"changelog.html#added"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changed - Changelog","doc":"- Go module updated to `whatsmeow v0.0.0-20260421083005-5b8886176ff7`,\n  `modernc.org/sqlite v1.50.0`, `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.36.11`.\n- README marked 0.2.0 status; usage section now reflects the working\n  pairing/send flow.\n\n## [0.1.0] - 2026-04-27","ref":"changelog.html#changed"},{"type":"extras","title":"Added - Changelog","doc":"- `ExWahaNative.Wire` вҖ” length-prefixed JSON framing for the Elixir <-> Go\n  bridge protocol with stream decoding and request-correlation refs.\n- `ExWahaNative.Bridge` вҖ” Port-owning GenServer that manages the Go process,\n  serializes outbound requests, correlates responses, dispatches async\n  events to the right Session.\n- `ExWahaNative.Session` вҖ” per-account GenServer holding status, QR, and\n  subscribers; routes outbound calls through the Bridge.\n- `ExWahaNative.Session.{Registry, Supervisor}` вҖ” registry + dynamic\n  supervisor for Session processes.\n- `ExWahaNative.Account` вҖ” account struct identifying a session and its\n  store backend.\n- `ExWahaNative.Provider` вҖ” implements `ExWaha.Provider` so calls go through\n  the unified facade.\n- `Mix.Tasks.ExWahaNative.BuildNative` вҖ” `mix ex_waha_native.build_native`\n  compiles the Go bridge binary with optional `--target` cross-compilation.\n- Go bridge skeleton (`native/bridge/main.go`) вҖ” stdio loop, JSON framing,\n  `ping` handler, stub handlers for the planned ops.","ref":"changelog.html#added-1"},{"type":"extras","title":"Known limitations - Changelog","doc":"- `whatsmeow` is not yet integrated on the Go side. All ops except `ping`\n  return `{\"ok\": false, \"code\": \"not_implemented\"}`. Wiring is the focus\n  of 0.2.0.\n- `ExWahaNative.Provider.parse_event/2` and `verify_signature/3` are\n  stubs вҖ” events flow over the bridge directly, not through HTTP webhooks.","ref":"changelog.html#known-limitations"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}